to the mysticism of Lao Tzu and Chuang Tzu. Schipper shows the fundamental unity underlying all aspects of Taoism as Taoism considers itself to be. The social body—the community, the village, the land—corresponds in all aspects to the physical body in Taoism. In both of them the survival of humanity is decided here and now. "My destiny is within me, not in Heaven!"  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aReligion. 4aTaoism (see also PHILOSOPHY. 4aTaoist). 7aRELIGION / Taoism (see also PHILOSOPHY / Taoist).2bisacsh1 aDuval, Karen C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGiradot, Norman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGirardot, Norman, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchipper, Kristofer, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000z97831106353480 cprintz978052008224340uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052035484540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520354845423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520354845/original  a978-3-11-063534-8  University of California Press Package Archive Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles